'''Ferrexpo plc''' ({{lse|FXPO}}) is a leading [[Switzerland|Swiss]]-based [[iron-ore]] producer operating in [[Ukraine]]. It is a constituent of the [[FTSE 250 Index]].

==History==
The business was founded in [[1960]] to exploit [[iron-ore]] reserves in [[Poltava]] in [[Ukraine]].<ref name=CFO>[http://www.ambition.co.uk/news/1243-Ferrexpo-appoints-new-CFO Ferrexpo appoints new CFO] Ambition, 3 December 2007</ref> The business was privatised in [[2001]] by the Ukrainian Government. In [[1977]] it started selling its product in the form of [[Pelletizing|pellets]]. It was first listed on the [[London Stock Exchange]] in [[2007]].<ref name=CFO/>

==Operations==
The Company sells most of its product to the steel mills of [[Eastern Europe]].<ref>[http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/markets/article3594234.ece Ferrexpo has attractions despite founder<U+2019>s big slice]</ref> It is organised into the following units:
* [[Ukraine]] - [[mining]] and sale of [[iron ore]]
* [[Switzerland]] - sale of [[iron ore]]

==Ownership==
The founder, [[Kostyantin Zhevago]], owns 51% of the company.<ref>[http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/article1908988.ece Ferrexpo must show its mettle to woo investors]</ref>

